											<section class="main bio authorbio">
							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/hannah-hoag/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Hannah Hoag is a journalist and editor based in Toronto. She works in the health, science, and climate units at the CBC. She previously worked at <i data-stringify-type="italic">The Conversation Canada</i> and Arctic Deeply, and co-wrote <i data-stringify-type="italic">The Science Writers’ Handbook</i>. Her work has also appeared in the <i data-stringify-type="italic">New York Times</i>, <i data-stringify-type="italic">The Atlantic</i>, <i data-stringify-type="italic">Science</i>, <i data-stringify-type="italic">Nature</i>, the <i data-stringify-type="italic">Globe and Mail</i>, and elsewhere.</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="520" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/HH_square-520x520.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="writter Hannah Hoag" decoding="async" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/HH_square-520x520.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/HH_square-150x150.jpg 150w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/HH_square-768x768.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/HH_square-900x900.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/HH_square.jpg 1032w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
